CHAPTER 2. VAT reform
Adopt legislation to reform the VAT system that will be effective as of July 1, 2015.
The reform will target a net revenue gain of 0.93 percent of GDP on an annual basis from parametric changes.
The new VAT system will:
(i) unify the rates at a standard 23 percent rate and a reduced 13 percent rate for food, energy, water, and hotels, and a superreduced rate of 6 percent for pharmaceuticals, books, and theater;
(ii) streamline exemptions to broaden the base; and
(iii) maintain the 30% discount on islands.